You need a Document Center / Employee 201 Module. Do not make 201, NTE, and NOD as random pages. Put them inside the employee profile and HR document workflow.
1. Where to put it in the system
Sidebar:
HR
 ├── Employees
 ├── 201 Files
 ├── Documents
 └── Disciplinary
Inside each employee profile:
Employee Profile
 ├── Personal Info
 ├── Employment Info
 ├── Attendance
 ├── Payroll
 ├── Leaves
 ├── Loans
 ├── 201 File
 ├── Disciplinary
 └── Audit History
2. 201 File Module
The 201 file is the complete employee record.
Each employee must have a digital 201 folder containing:
Personal Information
Employment Contract
Government IDs
Resume / CV
Application Form
Job Offer
Medical Records
Training Certificates
Performance Evaluations
Payslip / Payroll Documents
Leave Records
Warnings
NTE
NOD
Clearance
Resignation Letter
COE
Final Pay Documents
201 File features
Your devs should build:
Upload document
Tag document type
Set visibility
Set expiry date
Request missing document
Approve/reject uploaded document
Download document
Archive document
Audit trail
Document statuses
Pending Upload
Uploaded
For Review
Approved
Rejected
Expired
Archived
Database table
employee_documents
- id
- employee_id
- document_type
- document_title
- file_path
- status
- visibility
- expiry_date
- uploaded_by
- reviewed_by
- reviewed_at
- remarks
- created_at
- updated_at
Visibility:
HR only
Manager view
Employee view
Payroll view
Admin only
3. NTE Module — Notice to Explain
NTE is used when the employee has an incident/violation and the company asks for their written explanation.
Put it under:
Employee Profile → Disciplinary → Create NTE
Or:
HR → Disciplinary → New Case
NTE workflow
1. HR creates incident case
2. HR selects employee
3. HR selects violation type
4. HR writes incident details
5. System generates NTE document
6. NTE is sent/released to employee
7. Employee submits explanation
8. HR reviews explanation
9. Case moves to decision stage
NTE fields
Case number
Employee name
Position
Department
Incident date/time
Incident location
Violation type
Policy violated
Incident description
Evidence attachments
Deadline to respond
HR/person issuing NTE
Employee explanation field
Acknowledgment status
NTE statuses
Draft
Issued
Acknowledged
Explanation Submitted
No Response
Under Review
Closed
Moved to NOD
Database tables
disciplinary_cases
- id
- case_number
- employee_id
- violation_type
- incident_date
- incident_location
- description
- policy_reference
- status
- created_by
- created_at
nte_records
- id
- case_id
- employee_id
- response_deadline
- nte_document_id
- issued_at
- acknowledged_at
- employee_explanation
- explanation_submitted_at
- status
4. NOD Module — Notice of Decision
NOD is generated after HR reviews the employee explanation and decides the action.
Put it under:
Disciplinary Case → Create NOD
NOD workflow
1. HR reviews NTE explanation
2. HR selects decision
3. HR selects sanction, if any
4. System generates NOD
5. Employee receives NOD
6. Employee acknowledges
7. Case is closed or sanction is monitored
NOD decision types
No violation found
Verbal warning
Written warning
Final warning
Suspension
Termination
Salary deduction, if allowed by policy/law
Training required
Performance improvement plan
NOD fields
Case number
Employee name
Incident summary
Employee explanation summary
Findings
Decision
Sanction
Effective date
Duration, if suspension
Return-to-work date
Authorized signatory
Acknowledgment section
NOD statuses
Draft
Issued
Acknowledged
Sanction Active
Completed
Closed
Database table
nod_records
- id
- case_id
- employee_id
- decision
- sanction_type
- sanction_start_date
- sanction_end_date
- decision_details
- nod_document_id
- issued_at
- acknowledged_at
- status
